2. Read No. 3 here. In a letter dated October 05, 2023, the Commissionerate of Health Services issued a circular to the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare. Some amendments are proposed in the Government Decision dated 09.11.2021. Read No. 2 here. The Government was under consideration to amend the Government Decision dated 09.11.2021.
Considering the proposal of the Commissioner of Health Services, the Government Decision dated 09.11.2021 is being amended as follows: -
Government Decision No: Finance-2020 / Q.73 / Budget
table_trans: Issue No.11 of Annexure A to the Government Decision dated 09.11.2021: The Deputy Director of Health Services, (Circles) shall have the power to grant technical approval to expenditure on schemes under the Government Decision D. 28.09.2016. However, the proposals for accounting headings, innovative schemes not included in this Government Decision shall be subject to technical approval from the Office of the Commissioner Health Services, Commissionerate, Mumbai.

The Deputy Director Health Services, (Circles) shall have the power to grant technical approval to the drugs and consumables in the EDL / SCL / SDL list. (b) Technical approval / procurement of drugs and consumables other than the EDL / SCL / SDL list shall not be done at the level of District Surgeons and District Health Officers, Zila Parishad. (a) The Deputy Director Health Services (Circles) concerned shall have the power to grant technical approval to the equipment, machinery and materials in the possession of the District Surgeons. (e) The Deputy Director Health Services (Circles) shall have the power to grant technical approval to the District Council under the Zila Parishad for the equipment, machinery and materials in the District Health Officer, Zila Parishad (General, Tribal Schemes / Sub-Plan and all others) under the innovative scheme.

table_trans: The Deputy Director of Health Services, (Circles) concerned shall have both the powers to grant approval and technical approval to the proposal from the District Surgeon. However, the proposals of the Department of Public Health, Government Decision No. Earths-2020 / Q.73 / Budget Decision No. 09 / Budget Dec. 2021, which are not included in the Government Decision, shall be accorded technical approval by the Office of the Commissioner of Health Services, Commissionerate, Mumbai.
